name: Queue

aliases.name: Queue
aliases.comment:
A queue is a sequence supporting O(1) appending (`push`) of a new
    element to the back and amortizsed O(1) removal of the element at the
    front (`pop`).

values.name: empty
values.comment: An empty queue, ready for pushin'.

values.name: pop
values.comment:
Get the first element of the queue and the queue with the first element
    removed. Returns nothing if the queue is empty. Amortized O(1).
values.type: Queue.Queue a -> Maybe.Maybe ( a, Queue.Queue a )

values.name: push
values.comment: Put the given element at the back of the given queue. O(1).

values.name: toList
values.comment:
A list consisting of the elements in the order in which they were put into the
    queue (i.e., "front to back").

name: Queue.Internal
comment:
Internal representation of the queue type.
